# Golden cast for the loto whoami scene (docs/design/loto-demo-sketch.md).
# Pins the exact asciinema v2 bytes `fo --format cast` emits: clean cumulative
# timestamps (no float drift), measured geometry, full-redraw frames.
# Regenerate with: UPDATE_SCRIPTS=1 go test ./cmd/fo -run TestScripts
stdin whoami.in
fo --format cast --no-state
cmp stdout whoami.cast

-- whoami.in --
# fo:scene title="loto: every session has a handle" actors="AliceTester,BobTester"

## 01 В· two agents land in the same repo

> a fresh session needs to know what it's called.

> loto pins a handle from $LOTO_AGENT_ID вЂ” same env var, two different agents, two different identities.

@AliceTester $ loto whoami
  AliceTester

> Bob opens his own session, same repo, different env.

@BobTester $ loto whoami
  BobTester

> identity is stable per-session: Alice never appears as Bob.
-- whoami.cast --
